The "Indra Weather App" is a sophisticated weather forecasting system designed to revolutionize how users interact with weather information.
Leveraging the power of Python GUI and MySQL, this application offers a user-friendly interface for accessing real-time and accurate weather data.
With a focus on performance, reliability, and security, Indra provides a seamless experience, ensuring users can make informed decisions based on personalized forecasts. 
The system's scalability accommodates growing data and user demands, while its cross-platform compatibility ensures widespread accessibility.
Indra embodies a commitment to usability, maintainability, and compliance with regulatory standards,
making it a robust and indispensable tool for individuals seeking reliable weather insights in their daily lives.

Built with Python for the frontend, json, Python and MySQL for backend, and integrates with OpenWeatherMap API for accurate weather data.

Note: Requires internet connection for live updates.

Version: 1.0.0
Author: Rida Fatima

For detailed API documentation, visit www. https://openweathermap.org/guide.
